title: Deputy Chairman Senate Syedal Khan congratulates Bilal Farooq Tarar
content:
ISLAMABAD, Nov 8 (APP): Deputy Chairman Senate, Syedal Khan, has extended heartfelt congratulations to Pakistan Muslim League (N) candidate Bilal Farooq Tarar on his victory in the NA-66 by-election.

Bilal Farooq Tarar’s success reflects the people’s strong confidence in him as well as in the public-friendly policies of the Pakistan Muslim League (N), said the deputy chairman in a message issued by his office on Saturday.

He added that this victory is a clear testament to the trust and support the people continue to place in the leadership of PML-N for the progress and stability of the country.

Syedal Khan paid rich tribute to the leadership of Prime Minister Mian Muhammad Shehbaz Sharif, PML-N Quaid Mian Muhammad Nawaz Sharif, and Chief Minister Punjab Maryam Nawaz Sharif, acknowledging their visionary, tireless, and dynamic leadership.

He said that the collective vision of Nawaz Sharif, the relentless efforts of Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif, and the proactive leadership of Maryam Nawaz Sharif form the true foundation of the party’s ongoing success and public trust.

The Deputy Chairman further remarked that the free, fair, and peaceful conduct of the by-election reflects the strength of democratic continuity and public confidence in the system. He said Bilal Farooq Tarar’s victory stands as yet another testament to the PML-N’s enduring popularity among the masses.
